<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Aean on 04-04-2001 01:42 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Scenario A-Z it dont' matter cause no one owns a spawn, until someone has actually engaged the MoB it's free for anyone. 

The problem is then your conscience. Would I do that to someone? Probably not but under the right circumstances I would, if I myself had been camping it for a long time and took a break then came back to it or if the person camping it is lower level and has no chance in hell to get the MoB. 

Need before greed i think should also apply to people not in your guild. Helping someone out who is in need will only pay off for you later on in your levels. I've had people I gave money to in order to buy their 1st level spells only to have them give me something when they've surpased me in levels. So maybe by judging who needs the weapon more you can make a friend for life  :) or an enemy:P

I don't like it but there are politics when you get to the higher levels and someone may not own the spawn but they could have been camping it for a long time and get very disgruntled when you bring the wrecking crew in. Then it looks bad on you and your guild.

I dunno, i don't ever want that bloody thing and i'm at work and bored out of my skull and babbling. I think each situation needs to be looked at individually and you judge, the important thing is to know when you are wrong and do the right thing, and if you're right then handle it in the best way you can without hurting peoples egos. or just ks em all and let Marr sort em out!!  :)

